---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Wix vs Squarespace 2025: Flexibility vs Design',
  description: 'Wix vs Squarespace: Wix ($17-159/month) offers maximum flexibility with drag-and-drop editor. Squarespace ($16-65/month) offers design-first approach with polished templates. Wix: more control, more apps, cheaper entry. Squarespace: better templates, stronger e-commerce, easier. Choose Wix for flexibility. Choose Squarespace for design.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Wix vs Squarespace', 'website builder comparison', 'no-code platforms', 'Wix review', 'Squarespace review'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0C6EFC]/5 to-[#E04F5F]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0C6EFC] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Comparison · 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Wix vs Squarespace
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Wix and Squarespace are the two giants of DIY website building. Wix offers maximum flexibility with a drag-and-drop editor that lets you customize anything. Squarespace offers design-first simplicity with polished templates that look great out of the box. Wix gives you control. Squarespace gives you ease. Wix has more apps and integrations. Squarespace has stronger e-commerce. Both work. Neither is universally better.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Wix if you want maximum design control and flexibility. Choose Squarespace if you want something that looks beautiful with minimal effort and need stronger e-commerce. Wix is cheaper for similar features. Squarespace is easier if you have zero design experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Wix</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Squarespace</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of Use</td>
            <td class="p-4">Flexible but more complex</td>
            <td class="p-4">Simpler, template-driven</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design Flexibility</td>
            <td class="p-4">Maximum control</td>
            <td class="p-4">Template constraints</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Templates</td>
            <td class="p-4">Huge selection, varied quality</td>
            <td class="p-4">Fewer, consistently excellent</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">E-commerce</td>
            <td class="p-4">Good, more apps available</td>
            <td class="p-4">Strong, built-in features</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Apps Market</td>
            <td class="p-4">Massive, 300+ apps</td>
            <td class="p-4">Smaller, curated selection</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Pricing</td>
            <td class="p-4">$17-159/month</td>
            <td class="p-4">$16-65/month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best For</td>
            <td class="p-4">Control, flexibility seekers</td>
            <td class="p-4">Design, simplicity seekers</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wix Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Wix Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Maximum Design Freedom</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix's drag-and-drop editor lets you customize anything.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Want to break the grid? Add elements anywhere? Create unique layouts? Wix lets you. Squarespace templates are more rigid. Wix gives you pixel-perfect control over your design.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Massive App Market</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">300+ apps for everything from booking to marketing.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Need a specific feature? There's probably an app for it. Squarespace has fewer integrations. Wix's app market means you can extend functionality without coding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">More Template Variety</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Huge template selection for every industry.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Squarespace has ~100 templates. Wix has 800+. If you want options, Wix delivers. Quality varies more than Squarespace, but variety is unmatched.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Better for Content-Heavy Sites</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix started with blogs. Content management is in its DNA.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> For blogs, publications, content-heavy sites, Wix excels. The blogging features are more mature. Squarespace can do content but Wix is stronger here.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Cheaper Entry Point</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wix's paid plans start slightly cheaper than Squarespace.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If budget is tight, every dollar matters. Wix gives you similar features for slightly less money on entry-level plans.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Squarespace Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Squarespace Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Better Templates Out of the Box</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace templates are consistently excellent.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Wix has more templates but quality varies. Squarespace templates are all professional, modern, and polished. You can't make a bad-looking site with Squarespace.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Stronger E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace has better built-in e-commerce features.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Abandoned cart recovery, subscriptions, advanced shipping - Squarespace includes these. Wix has e-commerce but Squarespace is more mature for online stores.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Easier for Beginners</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace's template approach is simpler than Wix's editor.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you've never built a website, Squarespace is friendlier. Pick a template, swap content, publish. Wix's flexibility can be overwhelming for total beginners.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">More Polished Design Language</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace sites have a consistent, premium look.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Wix sites can look messy if you're not careful. Squarespace's design constraints prevent bad design. Your site will look professional, even if you have no design sense.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Better Performance Optimization</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace handles optimization automatically.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Wix gives you more control, which means more opportunities to slow down your site. Squarespace optimizes automatically. Your site loads fast without technical knowledge.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Wix Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Light:</strong> $16/month annually (or $23 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Core:</strong> $27/month annually (or $36 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business:</strong> $36/month annually (or $45 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business VIP:</strong> $159/month annually (or $199 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business E-commerce:</strong> $27-159/month depending on plan</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Annual savings:</strong> 25-50% off when billed annually.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Squarespace Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Personal:</strong> $16/month annually (or $23 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business:</strong> $23/month annually (or $33 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Basic:</strong> $27/month annually (or $36 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Advanced:</strong> $49/month annually (or $65 monthly)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Annual savings:</strong> 30-40% off when billed annually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Wix If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You want maximum control:</strong> Drag-and-drop freedom</li>
          <li>• <strong>You need specific apps:</strong> Wix's app market has everything</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're building a blog:</strong> Wix has better content features</li>
          <li>• <strong>You care about budget:</strong> Wix is slightly cheaper</li>
          <li>• <strong>You like to customize:</strong> Want to break templates, create unique layouts</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Squarespace If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You want it easy:</strong> Pick template, swap content, done</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're selling products:</strong> Better e-commerce features</li>
          <li>• <strong>You have zero design experience:</strong> Templates prevent bad design</li>
          <li>• <strong>You care about aesthetics:</strong> Consistently beautiful templates</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want something simple:</strong> Less overwhelming than Wix</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Wix and Squarespace both work. Wix offers maximum flexibility at the cost of complexity. Squarespace offers design simplicity at the cost of control. Wix has more apps and integrations. Squarespace has better templates and e-commerce. Wix gives you freedom to make mistakes. Squarespace prevents mistakes through constraints.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Wix for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Maximum design control and flexibility</li>
        <li>• Massive app market for integrations</li>
        <li>• Content-heavy sites and blogs</li>
        <li>• Unique, custom layouts</li>
        <li>• Slightly lower pricing</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Squarespace for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Beautiful templates out of the box</li>
        <li>• Strong e-commerce features</li>
        <li>• Easier beginner experience</li>
        <li>• Consistent, professional design</li>
        <li>• Better performance optimization</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't decide?</strong> Start with Squarespace if you have zero design experience. Start with Wix if you want to customize everything. Both offer free trials - test both and see which interface clicks. You can't go wrong with either choice.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-vs-squarespace" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Squarespace</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Modern vs established</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code vs open source</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
